On Thu, 26 Jun 2003 tjaspers(-at-)ameripath.com wrote:

> 2) Is it legal to buy a fairly new Bay window Bus from Mexico, swap the vin
> tags and frame pieces and call it an American 1973 Bus?

No, that would be too easy!  The problem is that the frame of a bus is a
welded part of the body, not a separate replaceable part like the bug.
You could probably do some less-than-kosher things to accomplish the same
thing, but be very careful!  The customs people don't fool around.

 > > 3) Did they ever produce the Vanagon in
Mexico? >

No.

> 4) How about the Thing, and all the Type3 VWs like hte squareback,
